<h1>Leonardo da Vinci<div id = "title">1452-1519</div></h1>
<h2>Basic Info About da Vinci</h2>
<p>Leonardo da Vinci was an artist and a philosopher. He liked to draw the things he saw. There is a theory for that: when he drew stuff then he thought about it more. Also da Vinci wrote in shorthand, and mirrored.</p><p>Da Vinci drew many pages on architecture, the human face, botany, physics, engineering, cartography, and anatomy. He also drew Mona Lisa and The Last Supper paintings.</p>
